Reasoning: The paper presents a formalisation of the pi-calculus using dependently-typed syntax and formal definitions of concurrency and causality. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with programming language semantics and concurrency, which are topics that fall under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also presents proofs and formal definitions, which aligns with the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with theoretical aspects of concurrency, which suggests that it may also belong to the Theory of Computation (cs.THEORY) sub-category.
